obedient /əˈbiːdɪənt/

1. ADJ A person or animal who is obedient does what they are told to do. 顺从的; 服从的 

例： He was very respectful at home and obedient to his parents. 他在家里很尊重人而且顺从父母。 

2. obedience N-UNCOUNT 顺从; 服从 

例： ...unquestioning obedience to the law. …对法律的绝对服从。

